Founded in 1998, The Permanent Data Company is based on more than twenty years of previous research by Steven Lacey about long term archiving and preservation of data in all forms. Utilizing proprietary platforms The Permanent Data Company has developed processes to photo chemically etch images of text and data into the surfaces of stainless steel, as well as various metal alloy groups. The end result is a metal protection master with a shelf life in excess of ten thousand years.

        In the usage of this process, government, publishers, motion picture studios, music publishers, insurance companies, investment and banking, and all commercial industry in need of protection from data loss, will have permanent storage and protection of documents, information, and media. The Permanent Data Company can replace commercially available, non permanent methods of data storage with permanent media recording film. Having completed early proof of concept tests, we are now poised to initiate comprehensive testing and validation of our processes.
